H0.text: where does cerebrospinal fluid flow to when it exits the cerebral aqueduct. Lateral ventricles

H1.text: where does cerebrospinal fluid flow to when it exits the cerebral aqueduct. Third ventricle

H2.text: where does cerebrospinal fluid flow to when it exits the cerebral aqueduct. Subarachnoid space

H3.text: where does cerebrospinal fluid flow to when it exits the cerebral aqueduct. fourth ventricle

A4.text: CSF can exit to the subarachnoid space through two lateral apertures and a single, midline median aperture.

A5.text: The fourth ventricle is the connector between the ventricular system (where CSF is produced) and the subarachnoid space (where CSF is absorbed).
